<HEADLINE> Sa Pinto suspended for hitting Portugal coach </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LISBON, April 1 (Xinhua) -- Ricardo Sa Pinto was suspended from
selection for Portugal's national team on Tuesday for hitting head
coach Artur Jorge last week.
</P>
<P>
The Portuguese Soccer Federation said in a statement it is
still investigating the incident and has yet to determined how
long Sa Pinto should be suspended.
</P>
<P>
Sa Pinto reportedly struck Jorge and knocked him down on
Wednesday at the national team's training ground in Lisbon, where
the team were preparing for a World Cup qualifier against Northern
Ireland.
</P>
<P>
The striker said later he hit Jorge because he was angry with
the coach for saying he had excluded him from the national side
because of disciplinary problems. 
</P>
</TEXT>
