<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zambian Border Residents Urged on Alert </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, April 1 (Xinhua) -- Zambian residents in Luapula
Province along the border with Zaire have been urged to be extra
vigilant and report all suspected illegal immigrants to the
authorities.
</P>
<P>
The appeal was made by Luapula Province Deputy Permanent
Secretary Norman Chibamba in Mansa, capital of Luapula Province
today, according to Zambia News Agency.
</P>
<P>
Chibamba said that the security system has been over stretched
because of the wide border with Zaire.
</P>
<P>
He said there is now a pressing need for effective and
constant monitoring on the Zambian border because of the danger
that some fleeing people from Zaire will use other illegal means
to enter Zambia.
</P>
<P>
He appealed to those who are harboring refugees ''not to allow
themselves to be used to these illegal immigrants. They should
report such suspected strangers to the authorities.''
</P>
<P>
As for the 1,000 refugees who had reportedly arrived in Mwense
district of Luapula Province over last weekend, Chibamba said
they went back to Zaire on Saturday after the situation in the
rebel-captured Kasenga improved.
</P>
<P>
He said the refugees only stayed on the Zambian side for one
day. He denied that all the 1,000 were Zairean soldiers who were
armed heavily. There are two Burundi soldiers who are being
looked after along with seven Zairean soldiers, according to
Chibamba. 
</P>
</TEXT>
