<HEADLINE> Unilever Boss Visits Zimbabwe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, April 1 (Xinhua) -- Visiting chairman of the food and
detergent manufacturing giant Unilever Plc Nial Fitzgerald said
here today the southern African region has the potential of
becoming Africa's economic powerhouse.
</P>
<P>
He told journalists after meeting Zimbabwean President Robert
Mugabe Zimbabwe and the region had many positive signs for
economic growth, chief among them being the prevailing peace.
</P>
<P>
''We are very optimistic about prospects of growth in the
region, especially given the political stability within the
region,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
Unilever, whose subsidiary company is Lever Brothers, also had
plans to expand its business in the country with particular
emphasis on the food industry.
</P>
<P>
He said Unilever was one of the largest investors in Africa.
</P>
<P>
Fitzgerald leaves here today for London after a business tour
of the region. 
</P>
