<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China, Ukraine to Boost Trade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, April 1 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Chinese Vice Premier Wu
Bangguo today met his Ukrainian counterpart, Viktor Pinzenik, and
the two vowed to boost bilateral trade.
</P>
<P>
Wu, who arrived on Monday for a two-day visit, said the two
countries should promote cooperation in trade in line with their
friendly relations.
</P>
<P>
He said there is great potential for trade cooperation due to
the two countries' complementary economies.
</P>
<P>
Wu noted mutual trust constitutes the basis for trade
cooperation, which has been fortified through frequent contacts
among leaders of both countries.
</P>
<P>
Pinzenik said the two governments should encourage businessmen
in the two countries to increase contacts.
</P>
<P>
Trade volume between Ukraine and China stood at 567 million
U.S. dollars in 1996, which put Ukraine as China's second largest
trade partner within the Commonwealth of Independent States.
</P>
<P>
But Ukrainian experts foresee a trade potential of 2 billion
dollars. There are more than 60 Chinese-Ukrainian joint ventures
in Ukraine and 23 in China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
