<BODY>
<HEADLINE> France Urges Immediate Resumption of </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 1 (Xinhua) -- France said today that the violent
incidents which have been taking place over the past several days
in the Palestinian territories showed "the emergency for the
immediate resumption of Israeli-Palestinian negotiations."
</P>
<P>
A French foreign ministry spokesman said that a "return to the
past" of the situation in the Palestinian territories cannot be
ruled out, referring to the Palestinian Intifadha (uprising) in
the late 1980s.
</P>
<P>
Two Palestinian militants were killed today by their own bombs
when they tried to make suicide bombing upon a school bus of young
Jewish settlers in the Gaza Strip, while a Palestinian policeman
was killed today by Israeli security forces in the West Bank.
</P>
<P>
"These tragic events showed once again the emergency for the
immediate resumption of Israeli-Palestinian negotiations on all
the questions in suspense, political and on security, in order
that the concluded agreements be strictly applied," said the
spokesman, Yves Doutriaux.
</P>
<P>
Prime Minister Benyamin Netanyahu of Israel said today that
Israel will not resume negotiations with the Palestinians "before
the Palestinian authority has proved in the field its will to
fight terrorism."
</P>
<P>
Asked about the decision by the Arab League to freeze the
normalization of relations between Israel and Arab nations, the
French foreign ministry spokesman said that the graveness of the
the situation calls for an immediate resumption of contacts
between Israel and Arab countries.
</P>
<P>
Violent clashes have been taking place on a daily basis between
Palestinians and Israeli security forces since Israel announced
its decision to build a new Jewish settlement in an Arab district
of East Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
The United States has criticized the decision by the Arab
League, saying that the latter should help create an atmosphere
which is favorable for peace. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
