<BODY>
<HEADLINE> France to Send 1,000 Soldiers to Albania in Int'l </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 1 (Xinhua) -- France will send 1,000 soldiers to
Albania to participate in the multinational protection force which
will arrive in the Balkan state before April 10, a French defense
ministry spokesman told Agence France-Presse (AFP).
</P>
<P>
The French troops will be deployed between the port city of
Durres and the capital Tirana, which are 40 kilometers from each
other, to make sure of the smooth sending of humanitarian goods to
Albanians.
</P>
<P>
The French soldiers will supervise the unloading of goods of
humanitarian aid at the port of Durres and guard the road between
Durres and Tirana to prevent the cargos of aid materials from
being robbed or deviated, the spokesman added.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman provided no details on which units of the French
army will be sent to Albania.
</P>
<P>
The chief of staff of the Italian army, Admiral Guido
Venturoni, said on Monday that Italy, which will command the
multinational protection force, will send 2,000 soldiers to
Albania and France will send 900 to 1,000.
</P>
<P>
Spain, Greece and Turkey have also decided to send troops to
Albania to participate in the mission decided by the Organization
for Security and Cooperation in Europe (OSCE) and approved by the
United Nations Security Council last Friday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
