<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 2 (Xinhua) -- The 14th International Building
and Construction Exposition is to be held in Hong Kong from June
11-14.
</P>
<P>
The fair is regarded as an effective marketing platform for
more than 300 leading edge companies to showcase a wide array of
advanced equipment, materials and services for the building and
construction industry in Hong Kong, South China as well as in
Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
During the four-day exhibition, international pavilions from
Australia, Italy, Britain, Mexico, Spain and the United States
will be featured.
</P>
<P>
The exposition consists of various specialized events such as a
computer show for the design and construction industry, an
international hardware exposition, and an international
construction machinery and equipment show.
</P>
<P>
According to Angelica Lim, group vice president of Building of
REED Exhibition Companies, the organizer of the exposition, the
fair aims to offer exhibitors the opportunity to become part of
the specialized shows during the four-day event, making it a
one-stop shopping event that satisfies the different needs of
individual buyers.
</P>
<P>
Lim said she expects the exposition to attract a more targeted
audience and make their visits more efficient and fruitful.
