<HEADLINE> International Chamber of Commerce Sets up Regional Office in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 2 (Xinhua) -- The International Chamber of
Commerce (ICC), a body representing business groups around the
world, has started the new year by opening a regional office for
Asia in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
ICC Secretary General Maria Livanos Cattaui said: "It is vital
for the ICC to strengthen its presence in Asia, whose vast and
growing markets are a stimulus to business throughout the world."
</P>
<P>
And the fact that the ICC has chosen Hong Kong for its only
regional office outside Paris where ICC is headquartered is a
reflection of world business' confidence in the city's future
after its return to China on July 1, she said.
</P>
<P>
"We are certain that Hong Kong will continue to flourish as one
of the world's leading commercial and financial centers," she
noted.
</P>
<P>
The ICC, founded in 1919 by a handful of business leaders,
groups thousands of member companies and associations from over
130 countries and regions.
</P>
<P>
The body's members in Hong Kong included the Hong Kong China
Manufacturers' Association, the Hong Kong Association of Banks,
Hong Kong General Chamber of Commerce.
</P>
<P>
Cattaui also said the ICC will hold its world congress next
week in Shanghai, the metropolis in east China, with senior
Chinese leaders expected to be present.  
</P>
</TEXT>
