<HEADLINE> Hydropower Benefits 100 million Chinese Farmers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, April 2 (Xinhua) -- China's hydropower generation
witnessed rapid development during the past ten years, providing
more than 100 million rural people access to electricity.
</P>
<P>
These farmers are now wealthier on average than other farmers
in the country, said Tong Jiandong, director of the International
Center On Small Hydropower, which is based in the capital city of
East China's Zhejiang Province.
</P>
<P>
Tong made the remarks today at a seminar attended by officials
from the United Nations Development Program (UNDP), the
International Energy Foundation, China's Ministry of Foreign Trade
and Economic Cooperation, and the Ministry of Construction as well
as delegates from Canada, Nepal, India, Japan and China.
</P>
<P>
The participants will discuss how international organizations
and developed countries can help developing countries in
hydropower generation, believing that such international
assistance can help poorer countries develop their economy while
contributing to a cleaner world environment.
</P>
<P>
Some Chinese provinces will also present some hydropower
projects at the seminar tomorrow, in the hope of forming joint
ventures with foreign investors. 
</P>
