<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Industrial Survey Shows Prospects </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 2 (Xinhua) -- China has discovered both its
strong and weak points in industrial development, thanks to its
just-concluded third nationwide industrial survey.
</P>
<P>
Governments at all levels should make full use of the survey
data and work out feasible development strategies accordingly,
Chinese Vice-Premier Zou Jiahua said today during a final review
meeting on the two-year study.
</P>
<P>
And the data must be published and data bases built, he added.
</P>
<P>
The survey aims to help learn more about China's industrial
structure and problems which have arisen in industrial development
and technological upgrading, he said.
</P>
<P>
More than five million people participated in the survey across
the country, with the return rate of the circulated survey forms
reaching nearly 100 percent. And 500 million data have been
collected, with an error rate of only 0.47 percent.
</P>
<P>
The Vice-Premier attributed the successful survey to powerful
organization and leadership at all levels, as well as scientific
and unified programs. He praised the high quality and efficiency
in data processing done by computers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
