<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Belarus, China Develop Positive Relations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Relations between Belarus and
China are developing in a "positive and practical" direction,
visiting Belarussian deputy prime minister V.V. Rusakevich told
Xinhua in an interview today.
</P>
<P>
Repeated exchange of visits by high-ranking leaders between the
two countries have laid a solid foundation for developing
bilateral relations, economic and trade cooperation, and
cooperation in other fields, since the two countries established
diplomatic relations, he said, Last year's bilateral trade volume
exceeded 100 million US dollars, nearly twice the figure of two
years ago, he added.
</P>
<P>
"This shows clearly that the bilateral trade maintains a good
development momentum," he said.
</P>
<P>
There is great potential for the two sides to develop trade,
and a series of agreements have been reached in the fields of
electronics, machinery, and the chemical industry. The Belarussian
Government will make positive steps, together with China, to
fulfill those agreements, he said.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that the two countries have broad prospects to
strengthen cooperation in culture, science and technology, and
education. Contacts and cooperation in those fields will increase
understanding and trust between the two peoples, and promote
cooperation in trade and other aspects.
</P>
<P>
The deputy prime minister spoke highly of the great
achievements China has made since it adopted the policy of reform
and opening up to the outside world, adding that his country "will
use China's successful experience for reference."
</P>
<P>
Rusakevich, heading an economic and trade delegation, arrived
in Beijing on Tuesday at the invitation of China Council for the
Promotion of International Trade.  
</P>
</TEXT>
