<HEADLINE> Alphand Likely to Compete in Winter Olympics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, April 2 (Xinhua) - Overall World Cup alpine skiing
champion Luc Alphand of France said he was too young to retire and
would like to compete in 1988 Winter Olympics, a press report
said here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The 31-year-old Frenchman said during a visit to his ski
company in Altenmarkt: "I feel too young to retire and would
really like to participate in the 1998 Winter Olympics in
Nagano. But I have to take my family into consideration."
</P>
<P>
But he added that he will decide about his future in Alpine
skiing in June. 
</P>
</TEXT>
