<HEADLINE> Indian Parliament to Hold Special Session on </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, April 2 (Xinhua) -- A one-day special session of Lok
Sabha (the lower house of parliament) will be convened on April 11
to allow the 14-party United Front government led by H.D. Deve
Gowda to seek a vote of confidence, it was officially announced
here today.
</P>
<P>
Lok Sabha, which adjourned on March 21 until April 21, will now
resume its sitting on April 11, a Lok Sabha secretariat press
release said.
</P>
<P>
Subject to exigencies of government business, the sitting of
the Lok Sabha shall conclude on that day itself, the release said.
</P>
<P>
A Lok Sabha official said the decision was made after the
secretariat received a message from the government to call a
session of the house on April 11 to discuss urgent business.
</P>
<P>
Indian President Shanker Dayal Sharma has asked Gowda to prove
his majority by April 11 following the Congress party's withdrawal
of support for the 10-month-old government on Sunday, a move which
reduced the coalition to a minority.
</P>
<P>
Both houses of parliament adjourned on March 21 for a
month-long recess in the budget session to enable parliamentary
standing committees related to various ministries to scrutinize
the budget proposals presented by the United Front government.
</P>
</TEXT>
