<HEADLINE> U.S. Vessel Crewmen Arrested in Greece for Oil Leak </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Greece arrested the captain and an
engineer of a U.S. cargo vessel today for oil leak into the
Saronic Gulf, northern Greece, which has caused sea pollution.
</P>
<P>
The oil slick caused by the vessel covered about 100 square
meters near the port of Keratsini in the gulf, the Athens News
Agency (ANA) reported.
</P>
<P>
The slick was discovered early this morning and an
investigation conducted by local coast guard officers revealed
that the U.S. vessel, which was moored at a pier in Keratsini,
should be responsible for the incident.
</P>
<P>
A special team was immediately called in by the Greek
government to clean up the oil slick on the sea.
</P>
<P>
The two arrested U.S. crewmen would appear in a Greek court
later today, local reports said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
