<HEADLINE> Broadcasts Mark Inner Mongolia's 50th Anniversary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 2 (Xinhua) -- China Radio International is
planning a series of programs in 43 languages to be broadcast all
over the world to mark the 50th anniversary of the Inner Mongolia
Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
The programs started Tuseday and will last for four and a half
months, covering 24 topics on the great changes that have taken
place in the region's politics, economy, industry, agriculture,
animal husbandry, cultural progress, education, science and
technology and tourism.
</P>
<P>
They are intended to help people in the rest of the world learn
more about Inner Mongolia, the oldest autonomous region in New
China, sources at China Radio said.
</P>
<P>
The station will have contests accompanying the broadcasts in
English, German, Japanese, Russian, Mongolian, and Urdu, and six
contest winners will be invited to visit Inner Mongolia.
</P>
<P>
The radio station has held similar broadcasts many times,
greatly helping local economic and social development.  
</P>
</TEXT>
