<HEADLINE> Islamic Jihad Denies Responsibility For Gaza </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, April 2 (Xinhua) -- The Islamic Jihad Movement today
categorically denied any responsibility for two bombings near two
Jewish settlements in the Gaza Strip Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The two bombings took place at Kfar Daroum and Netzarim,
killing two Palestinians and wounding five others.
</P>
<P>
At a press conference held at the headquarters of journalist
association in Gaza this morning, Abdallah Al-Shami, an Islamic
Jihad leader, said:"Jihad Movement in Palestine declares from the
Gaza Strip, as it declared outside by its leader Dr. Ramadan
Shalah, that it has no connection with the two suicide bombings,"
according to a report of JMCC, an East Jerusalem-based Palestinian
press service.
</P>
<P>
He added that "the occupation authorities and their elements
were convicted (of the crime)."
</P>
<P>
The Israeli authorities claimed Tuesday that the state-run
Israel Radio received separately anonymous calls saying the
Islamic Resistance Movement (Hamas) and Islamic Jihad they
belonged to were responsible for the two attacks.
</P>
<P>
Hamas officials in Gaza immediately denied their group had
anything to do with the incidents.
</P>
<P>
Al-Shami confirmed reports that Palestinian police had arrested
a number of Jihad activists in the Gaza Strip, including his
nephew. 
</P>
</TEXT>
