<HEADLINE> China, EU Seek Cooperation Opportunities in Multimedia Field </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Hundreds of officials, experts,
and businessmen from China and European Union member countries
gathered here today to discuss possibilities for their future
cooperation in multimedia applications for education and health
care.
</P>
<P>
The first Sino-EU conference on the information society,
co-sponsored by the State Science and Technology Commission (SSTC)
and EU General Directorate XIII, opened here today.
</P>
<P>
A SSTC official said at the opening ceremony that China is
ready to launch cooperation with the EU in the multimedia
applications and other high-tech fields.
</P>
<P>
An EU official said the EU will use part of its research fund
for projects that encourage developing countries to enter the
information society.
</P>
<P>
The official added that EU senior officials in charge of
scientific research, personnel training, information, and industry
plan to visit China this year and she believed that the visits
will serve to promote the Sino-EU science and technological
cooperation which started 16 years ago.
</P>
<P>
Another SSTC official said that in the past few years, the
established Sino-EU demonstration projects in information
technologies have yielded great social and economic achievements
in China and also helped push forward bilateral cooperation in
industry and trade. 
</P>
</TEXT>
