The all ordinaries index finished 3.0 points higher at 2,355.2,
off a low of 2,352.0 and a high of 2,369.3.
</P>
<P>
Yesterday, Australian shares plunged to their lowest level in
more than three months following a second consecutive nose-dive on
Wall Street.
</P>
<P>
Brokers said today's performance was disappointing as the
leading indicator had rallied higher during the day.
</P>
