<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Qian Qichen Meets Hong Kong Delegation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier Qian Qichen
today expressed the belief that so long as the entire Hong Kong
residents make concerted efforts and the principle of "one
country, two systems" is earnestly implemented, Hong Kong will
continue to maintain its prosperity and stability.
</P>
<P>
Qian made the remarks during a meeting with a delegation from
the Kowloon Chamber of Commerce of Hong Kong led by its chairman
Tong Kwok Wah.
</P>
<P>
He appreciated the efforts that the Kowloon Chamber of Commerce
has made in boosting Hong Kong's economy and promoting its smooth
return to the motherland.
</P>
<P>
Qian said that Hong Kong's return to the motherland is a major
event at the end of this century, which not only needs the
negotiations between the two governments of China and Britain, but
also the support from the six million Hong Kong compatriots.
</P>
<P>
He noted that Hong Kong has experienced a 13-year-long
transitional period and its smooth return to the motherland is a
foregone conclusion.
</P>
<P>
After its return, he said the Chinese government will adopt
the principle of "one country, two systems" towards Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
He said Under the pre-requisite of one country, it is
imperative to safeguard China's reunification and love the
country. "Two systems" mean the practising of two different
systems.
</P>
<P>
Qian said the principle of "one country, two systems" is a
pioneering undertaking, fully considering the interests of the
state, the Chinese nation, and the whole of the Chinese people
including the Hong Kong compatriots.
</P>
<P>
He assured the Hong Kong residents that to implement the
principle of "one country, two systems" is precisely to
continuously maintain its existing social, economic systems, and
their way of life, retain its existing independent taxation
system, and continue to circulate the Hong Kong dollar.
</P>
<P>
It has not only considered the customs of the Hong Kong
residents, but also the benefit to the country's economic growth
and the realization of its peaceful reunification, Qian said.
</P>
<P>
Tong said the Kowloon Chamber of Commerce has actively promoted
its investment in the Chinese mainland for many years. It is now
throwing itself into the celebrations for Hong Kong's return and
later will make greater efforts to the region's stable transition,
prosperity, and stability. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
