<HEADLINE> Australia To Provide Fund For Cambodian Elections </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Australia would provide 500,000
Australian dollars (392,000 US dollars) in aid for Cambodia's
forthcoming local elections due in December this year and national
elections due six months later.
</P>
<P>
In a statement, Foreign Affairs Minister Alexander Downer said,
"the importance of these elections is all the more evident after
Sunday's grenade attack in Phnom Penh", which killed 16 and
injured another 118.
</P>
<P>
The assistance will include training of electoral officials and
short-term assistance with preparations for the elections, there
will also be help on voter registration, voter education and
election management.
</P>
<P>
This will also involve a consultancy to examine options and
provide guidelines for the development of a database of polling
stations and their associated precincts.
</P>
<P>
Downer said the electoral support aid was part of Australia's
continuing commitment to the Cambodian peace process and the
strengthening of the country's democratic institutions.
</P>
<P>
These elections are the first ones since United Nations
supervised elections completed Cambodia's transition to democratic
rule in 1993. 
</P>
</TEXT>
