<HEADLINE> Chinese State Councillor Meets US Visitors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Chinese State Councillor Song Jian
told James Sensenbrenner, chairman of the House Science Committee
of the United States, that he hopes Sino-US scientific and
technological cooperation and exchanges can have still better
development.
</P>
<P>
During their meeting at the Great Hall of the People here this
afternoon, Song, who is also minister in charge of the State
Science and Technology Commission, welcomed Sensenbrenner who is
on his first visit to China.
</P>
<P>
Noting that Sino-US scientific and technological cooperation
and exchanges are important components of bilateral friendly
relations, Song said that over the past decade and more, bilateral
exchanges and cooperation in scientific and technological fields
have made great progress.
</P>
<P>
He went on to say that bilateral scientific and technological
cooperation have expanded continuously and the number of
cooperative projects between the two sides is on the rise.
</P>
<P>
He said he is convinced that Sensenbrenner's current visit to
China is expected to further strengthen cooperation between the
two parliaments in the scientific and technological fields, as
well as the growth of bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
Praising China's great progress in scientific and technological
fields in the process of reform and opening-up, Sensenbrenner said
that US-China scientific and technological cooperation is very
important.
</P>
<P>
He said the US legislative and executive departments support
such cooperation, hoping it can be developed better.
</P>
<P>
So far, there are over 30 bilateral agreements between the two
countries on scientific and technological cooperation that have
taken effect, and these agreements are of significance to the
exchanges between scientists of the two countries, Sensenbrenner
said.
</P>
<P>
Song also briefed Sensenbrenner and his party on China's
domestic situations and answered the questions raised by the US
visitors. 
</P>
</TEXT>
