<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Builds First Geothermal Power Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopia's first geothermal
power project, the Aluto-Langano Geothermal Project will be
completed early next year, the Ethiopian Electric Light and Power
Authority announced here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The project which is located 180 kms south of Addis Ababa, was
launched last August with a 103.5 million Birr (about 15.7
million Dollars) allotted by the Ethiopian government.
</P>
<P>
The power plant has a capacity to generate 7.2 mega watt
electric power from geothermal steam when it goes into operation.
</P>
<P>
According to the authority, the work of a 17 kms road leading
from the main road to the project site and the construction of
residential units for workers is being speeded up. 
</P>
</TEXT>
