<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading French Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 2 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news items
in leading French newspapers today.
</P>
<P>
Liberation:
</P>
<P>
-- The two suicide bombing attempts by two Palestinian
militants at school buses of Jewish settlers, and the death of two
Palestinians killed by Israeli soldiers, all of which took place
on Tuesday, showed the incapability of Israeli Prime Minister
Binyamin Netanyahu to contain violence in occupied territories.
</P>
<P>
Harassed by the requirements of his ultra-Orthodox allies and
threatened with diplomatic isolation by the Arab League, Netanyahu
has proposed to form a government of national union to negotiate
with the Palestinian Authority.
</P>
<P>
-- Italy today began to put on trial Algerian national Djamel
Lounici, who is believed to be the main organizer of an Islamic
arms smuggling network in Europe providing logistic support to
Islamic militants in Algeria. Detained by Italian authorities
since May 1995, Lounici, 34, was accused of murdering seven
Italian seamen in July 1994 on their ship at the Algerian port of
Djendjen, near Jijel.
</P>
<P>
Le Figaro:
</P>
<P>
-- The finance centers of Europe were hit by the fall at the
Wall Street on Tuesday, with the stock index at Frankfurt falling
by 3.88 percent, Amsterdam by 4.4 percent, London by 1.5 percent
and Paris 2.85 percent, the biggest since September 1995.
</P>
<P>
The rise of interest rates in the United States, and the fall
of the Dow Jones Index by 4.3 percent in two sessions, resulted in
a wave of selling of stocks in Europe, as the stocks were judged
over-valued after months of consistent rising. 
</P>
