<HEADLINE> Tour de France to Start from Ireland in 1998 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 2 (Xinhua) -- The Tour de France will start from
Ireland in 1998, organisers said here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
According to a report from Reuter, Tour de France boss
Jean-Marie Leblanc and Irish Tourism and Trade minister Enda Kenny
will sign the official agreement for the start on Thursday in
Dublin.
</P>
<P>
The start will be on the July 11-12 weekend to avoid clashing
with the 1998 soccer World Cup in France from June 10 to July 12.
</P>
<P>
Even though the Tour has started outside France 13 times in
the past, it will be the first time it is launched outside the
European mainland. 
</P>
