<HEADLINE> Chinese NPC Leader Arrives in Norway for Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OSLO, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Qiao Shi, chairman of the Standing
Committee of the National People's Congress (NPC), arrived here
this morning for a four-day official visit to Norway.
</P>
<P>
He came to visit at the invitation of President of the
Norwegian Parliament Kirsti Grondahl.
</P>
<P>
This is the first visit to the North European country by a
Chinese NPC leader.
</P>
<P>
Qiao was greeted at the airport by senior officials from the
Norwegian parliament and Chinese Ambassador to Norway Zhu Yinglu.
</P>
<P>
In a written statement issued at the airport, Qiao said that
his visit was aimed at enhancing the understanding and friendship
between the two peoples and strengthening cooperation between
China and Norway.
</P>
<P>
The two countries have attained a remarkable development in
bilateral relations in the political, economic, cultural and other
fields since they established diplomatic ties in 1954, Qiao said.
</P>
<P>
The exchanges between the Norwegian parliament and the NPC of
China is also increasing, he said.
</P>
<P>
To further consolidate and strengthen the Sino-Norwegian long
term and stable relationship of friendship and cooperation is not
only in the interests of the two countries and the two peoples but
also conducive to peace, stability and development in the world at
large.
</P>
<P>
"I am expecting to exchange views with Norwegian leaders in the
coming few days on further developing the friendly and cooperative
relations and issues of common interest," Qiao said.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese NPC leader is scheduled to meet King Harald V,
Prime Minister Thorbjoern Jagland and Parliamentary President
Kirsti Grondahl.
</P>
<P>
Before arriving here, he paid a six-day official visit to
France and had a brief stopover in Sweden.
</P>
<P>
Norway is the second leg of his Europe and Asia tour which will
also take him to Italy and Mongolia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
