<HEADLINE> French President Visits Czech Republic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 2 (Xinhua) -- French President Jacques Chirac left
here this afternoon for a two-day state visit to the Czech
Republic.
</P>
<P>
During the visit, he is expected to discuss with Czech
President Vaclav Havel the economic relations between the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
This is the first time for a French president to visit Prague
since President Francois Mitterrand visited there in December 1993.
</P>
<P>
Chirac is expected to reiterate France's support to the
integration of the central and eastern European countries,
including the Czech Republic, into the European Union and the
North Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO) by the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
The president is accompanied by a group of French business
leaders and government ministers including Minister of Justice
Jacques Toubon, Minister of European Affairs Michel Barnier,
Minister of the Interior Jean-louis Debre and Minister of Exterior
Trade Yves Galland.
</P>
<P>
During his visit, Chirac is scheduled to meet with
representatives of the French community in the Czech capital,
deliver a speech in the Czech parliament, and lay the first stone
for a future French school in Prague, sources from the Elysee
Presidential Palace said.
</P>
<P>
Interior Minister Jean-Louis Debre will sign with his Czech
counterpart a treaty on police cooperation and easing of visa
restrictions, the sources said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
