<HEADLINE> Chinese Company to Be Listed in Australia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Zhou Daojiong, chairman of the
China Securities Regulatory Commission has said a Chinese cement
producer is scheduled to list in Australia this year.
</P>
<P>
The Hebei Taihang Cement Co Ltd, a major subsidiary of the
Taihang Cement Group, which one of China's top three cement
producers, is expected to float 200 million (about 24 million US
dollars) to 300 million yuan in stocks in the Australian Stock
Exchange, according to the company's Board Chairman Zhao Bingji.
</P>
<P>
"Raising capital in the world securities market is a long-term
policy of the Chinese government and the trial listings of Chinese
companies overseas have proved to be a success," Zhou Daojiong,
told a symposium on listing Chinese companies in Australia Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Latest statistics show that 29 Chinese companies have been
listed overseas so far, raising more than 5.9 billion US dollars
in foreign capital.  
