<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Le Pen Phenomenon Drives French Jews to Israel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 2 (Xinhua) -- The continuous rise of the
extreme-right National Front (FN), headed by Jean-Marie Le Pen,
could make 7,000 to 10,000 French Jews to emigrate to Israel, the
Agence France-Presse quoted an Israeli immigration official as
saying today.
</P>
<P>
"This phenomenon frightens French Jews and I estimate that
7,000 to 10,000 among them could emigrate to Israel in the next
two years," said Yaguil Allouche, one of the leaders of the
semi-official institution of the Union of Jews in France and North
Africa (UNIFAN) in Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
He said that French Jews who have just emigrated to Israel was
also due to economic and religious reasons, but these
mobilizations become second important when compared with "the fear
caused by the success of the FN," a party which spread xenophobic,
racist and anti-Semite propaganda.
</P>
<P>
UNIFAN said that 4,298 French Jews emigrated to Israel from
1990 to 1994, while in 1996, 2,103 Jews left France for Israel, a
10 percent rise over 1,855 in 1995.
</P>
<P>
France now has a Jewish community of 650,000. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
