<HEADLINE> Share Prices Rise on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Share prices finished mixed on
the Singapore market while the benchmark Straits Times Industrials
Index gained 15.14 points to close at 2089.81 points today.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume stood at 139.94 million units, worth
321.93 million Singapore dollars (about 223.56 million US
dollars). Declines led advances 201 to 131, while 272 other
counters remained steady.
</P>
<P>
Excel was the most actively traded stock as it posted a
turnover of 11.39 million units. It was followed by Guthrie G
Warrant02 which had 7.16 million units traded. The United
Industrial Corporation (UIC) was next with 5.01 million of its
shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
The Singapore Press Holdings (SPH) Foreign again led the
gainers of the day as it rose by 80 cents to finish at 27.7
Singapore dollars. Local property developer City Developments
increased by 60 cents to close at 13.4 Singapore dollars, while
the City Development Warrant 98 and the Overseas Chinese Banking
Corporation (OCBC) Foreign gained 50 cents each to end at 10.6 and
17.6 Singapore dollars respectively.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, B Raya, Khong Guan, Malay Plantations, OUE,
Rashid Hussain, and South Bank Foreign Warrant shared the top spot
on the losers' list as each of them declined by 30 cents to end at
2.6, 4.3, 2.7, 6.5, 11.1, and 2.1 dollars respectively. Bolton
Warrant 01 was 22 cents lower at 1.03 dollars, while F&AMP;N fell by
20 cents to finish at 12 Singapore dollars.  
</P>
