<HEADLINE> HK PLC Members' Interests to Open to Public </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 2 (Xinhua) -- The Provisional Legislative
Council (PLC) of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region
(HKSAR) welcomes Hong Kong citizens to inspect the relevant
information on the registration of the interests of PLC members.
</P>
<P>
According to a press release issued here today by the PLC
secretariat, the inspection for the information will start from
April 7.
</P>
<P>
At its meeting on March 22, 1997, the PLC endorsed a resolution
to request all members to furnish particulars of their registable
interests to the secretariat no later than April 5.
</P>
<P>
The release said that the information will be available at the
PLC secretariat which is now at the fourth floor of Huaxia Art
Center in Overseas Chinese Town, Shenzhen City.
</P>
<P>
It said that citizens who wish to inspect the information
contained in the "Register of Members' Interests" can go to the
secretariat and they can get photocopies as well. 
</P>
