<HEADLINE> Thousands of Zimbabwean Villagers Appeal for Food </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Masvingo Province in south
Zimbabwe is appealing for food to feed thousands of villagers in
Mwenezi and Chiredzi districts who have run out of food, the
daily "The Herald" reported today.
</P>
<P>
Masvingo Provincial Administrator Alphonse Chikurira said
66,000 people in semi-arid Chiredzi district are in need of food
following an unfavorable agricultural season.
</P>
<P>
His office had sent an urgent appeal for assistance to the
National Committee on Grain Loan and is waiting for a response.
</P>
<P>
Chiredzi and Mwenezi districts fall within agro-ecological
region five which receives scant rains. The two districts again
failed to get meaningful rains, resulting in widespread crop
failure. 
</P>
