<HEADLINE> Foreign Investors Engaged in SA Bond Trades </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Foreign investors have
accounted for one fifth of all trading in South African bonds by
value since the beginning of 1997, local daily "The Star"
reported today.
</P>
<P>
The value of trades by non-residents almost triple in the
three months ended March 27 from a year earlier to 164.79 billion
Rands (37.45 billion U.S. Dollars).
</P>
<P>
This is equivalent to 19 percent of the total market volume of
282.77 billion Rands (64.26 billion U.S. Dollars) from 59.07
billion Rands (13.42 billion U.S. Dollars) in the previous year,
the Bond Exchange of South Africa was quoted as saying. 
</P>
