<BODY>
<HEADLINE> First Training Center For Sustained Coastal Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 2 (Xinhua) -- The Xiamen Sea Shore Sustainable
Development Training Center, the first of its kind in China, has
been established in Xiamen, a coastal city in east China's Fujian
Province.
</P>
<P>
The center was set up jointly by the Xiamen City government and
Xiamen University, according to the State Oceanic
Administration. As a famous sea port city, Xiamen has a sea area
accounting for one-fifth of its total area.
</P>
<P>
The center is designed to teach people how to develop marine
resources while protecting the ocean environment, provide the city
with a large number of senior managerial personnel with both
scientific knowledge and administrative skills.
</P>
<P>
It will also provide training for officials of the city
government and oceanic institutions, and will educate them in
oceanic administration in line with with the specific conditions
in Xiamen.
</P>
<P>
Training courses will also be held for officials and
technicians from other coastal cities, in an effort to spread
expertise gained from comprehensive management of the Xiamen
seashore, a pilot project co-sponsored by the United
Nations Development Program (UNDP), Global Environmental
Fund (GEF), and the International Maritime Organization.
</P>
<P>
The center will also co-operate with international
organizations in holding training programs on sea and land
environmental protection. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970402.0123 </DOCNO>
