<HEADLINE> East China Province Improving Lives of More Than Half Million </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, April 2 (Xinhua) -- East China's Shandong Province plans
to put more effort into a local aid-the-poor project to help
700,000 impoverished people set out on the road to a better life
this year.
</P>
<P>
By the end of the year the number of poverty-stricken people in
the province will drop significantly from as many as one million
to 300,000.
</P>
<P>
Although its economic development has been quite good, Shandong
still has a million needy people, mainly in 10 of its poorest
counties in mountainous areas or on the alluvial plain.
</P>
<P>
Last year the lives of more than 600,000 poor people in the 10
counties were improved when they became the first group to benefit
from the implementation of this provincial aid-the-poor project.
</P>
<P>
This year the province will speed the project up by adding 30
million yuan worth of cash and materials to it. 
</P>
