<DOCNO> XIE19970402.0125 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Utah's Malone Named NBA Player of the Month </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, April 1 (Xinhua) -- Utah Jazz forward Karl Malone,
who moved into 10th place on the NBA's all-time scorers list last
month, was named on Tuesday the NBA Player of the Month for March.
</P>
<P>
Malone led Utah to a franchise-best 14-1 mark by averaging 31.0
points, 9.0 rebounds and 4.2 assists per game, while shooting .591
from the field.
</P>
<P>
The 12-year veteran, who ranked first in scoring and eighth in
shooting percentage among league leaders in March, surpassed
Jerruy West on March 19 to move into the Top 10 and is 294 points
behind Alex English for ninth place.
</P>
<P>
He also joined Kareem Abdul-Jabbar, Wilt Chamberlain, Moses
Malone and Elvin Hayes on March 9 as the only players in MBA
history to score 25,000 points and grab 10,000 rebounds.
</P>
<P>
"I have always voted Malone for MVP, " said Utah head coach
Jerry Sloan. "In his whole career, he has only missed four
games. As hard as he works in the offseason, he should get some
credit. One thing I like about Karl is that there are no
sideshows, he just comes and plays hard."
</P>
<P>
Malone, who was nambed NBA Player of the Week twice during the
month, led the Jazz in scoring 14 times and scored 35 or more
points six times and 30 or more points 10 times. He had several
standout performances during the month including 41 points, seven
rebounds, six assists and two steals in a 111-104 win at Golden
State on March 3 and 41 points, six rebounds, four assists and one
steal in a 95-88 win over Detroit on March 7.
</P>
<P>
Other candidates for NBA player of the Month were Chicago's
Michael Jordan, Denver's Antonio McDyuess, Miami's Tim Hardaway,
New York's Patrick Ewing, Orlando's Anfernee Hardaway, Phoenix's
Keven Johnson and Washington's Chris Webber. 
</P>
</TEXT>
