<HEADLINE> Fuel Prices Reduced in Uganda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Fuel prices dropped slightly in
Uganda yesterday, reported the local daily "The New Vision"
today.
</P>
<P>
Of the three major fuels, diesel registered the most
significant price change, dropping by 30 Shillings per liter from
1,070 to 1,040 Shillings (about 1.05 to 1.02 US Dollars).
</P>
<P>
Petrol dropped by 10 Shillings to 1,150 Shillings (1.12
Dollars) per liter, while kerosene fell by 20 Shillings from 860
to 840 Shillings (about 0.84 to 0.82 Dollars) per liter.
</P>
<P>
It is the third time in a row this year that fuel pump prices
have experienced a downward trend. This is contrary to the trend
in last quarter of 1996 when the prices rose in the country.
</P>
<P>
According to industrial sources, the latest cuts were a result
on an appreciating Shilling and a drop in world prices plus a
reduction in duties by the Uganda Revenue Authority. 
</P>
</TEXT>
