<HEADLINE> Fire Outbreaks Rise in Uganda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Fire outbreaks in Uganda rose to
477 in 1996, representing an increase of 17.4 percent than 1995,
reported the local daily "The Monitor" today.
</P>
<P>
This is contained in the annual report of the fire brigade for
the year 1996.
</P>
<P>
According to it, out of these incidents, 281 were in and
around Kampala, capital of Uganda including areas within a
40-mile radius.
</P>
<P>
The report attributed the increase in the fire outbreaks to
the increased expansion of the city and other towns as well as
increased levels of economic activity in the country.
</P>
<P>
Kampala has the highest percentage of fire occurrence with 59
percent, followed by Jinja, major industrial city in the country
with 29.3 percent, it said.
</P>
<P>
In terms of monetary value, the report said that the total
value of damage suffered by the public as a result of fire in the
whole country is estimated at 2.8 million U.S. Dollars. 
</P>
