<HEADLINE> Chinese President Meets US Guests </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin met
here today with Willie Brown Jr., mayor of San Francisco in the
United States.
</P>
<P>
Jiang spoke highly of Brown's efforts for promoting friendly
ties and cooperation between China and US.
</P>
<P>
He said that since San Francisco is the international trade and
finance center along the Pacific coast in the US, as well as the
door to trade with the Asia-Pacific countries, it has played an
important role in Sino-US trade.
</P>
<P>
The city is also one of the places in the US where lots of
Chinese live, thus having established long-term and good ties with
China, he said.
</P>
<P>
San Francisco became twin city of Shanghai, China's largest
industrial city, soon after China and the US established
diplomatic ties in 1979.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that Brown's current visit will push forward San
Francisco's cooperation with Shanghai and other cities of China.
</P>
<P>
Brown said that as a mayor who was elected 15 months ago, he
would continue to further the existing good relations between San
Francisco and Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
He also said that he would continue to promote Sino-US
relations, especially the exchanges and cooperations between
business circles of San Francisco and China, he added.
</P>
<P>
Brown and his party are here at the invitation of Shanghai
Municipal Government.  
</P>
</TEXT>
