<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Courts Told to Earnestly Enforce Law </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Responding to criticisms from the
top legislature this March, President of the Supreme People's
Court Ren Jianxin has told courts nationwide to take effective
measures for earnest law enforcement.
</P>
<P>
Ren issued the call at a recent meeting of the Supreme People's
Court.
</P>
<P>
He said that the Fifth Session of the Eight National People's
Congress (NPC) concluded last month approved the work report of the
Supreme People's Court.
</P>
<P>
"While affirming the work of courts, deputies to the NPC also
put forth quite a number of criticisms and suggestions, which were
mainly centered on the problems of earnest in law enforcement,
efficiency, and the proficiency of judges," Ren said.
</P>
<P>
"Therefore, earnest law enforcement and up-grading the law
enforcement proficiency level shall be the central task of courts
across the country," he stressed.
</P>
<P>
He revealed that the Supreme People's Court will lead a law
enforcement inspection tour starting this month through the end of
June, attended by NPC deputies, to some localities.
</P>
<P>
Members of the National Committee of the Chinese People's
Political Consultative Conference, a top advisory body, will also
join the party.
</P>
<P>
Focus will be placed on local and departmental protectionism,
unfair judgement, and abuses of judicial power for personal
gain.
</P>
<P>
He called for relevant departments in the Supreme Court to take
up responsibilities to "clean" the courtrooms, and help to foster a
contingent of jurors and judges "able to stand all tests."
</P>
<P>
He urged all the court staff to study the new Criminal
Procedural Law and the Criminal Law and effectively use them as
weapons in dealing with crimes.
</P>
<P>
"Courts across the country should be further disciplined, and
their work efficiency improved," he said.
</P>
<P>
He expressed that hope that court staffs, with their
responsibilities to the Party and the people in mind, earnestly
perform their duties to make new contributions to the country's
reform, opening up and modernization drive by providing effective
legal guarantees. 
</P>
</TEXT>
