<HEADLINE> Jerry Sloan Named Coach of the Month </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, April 1 (Xinhua) -- Jerry Sloan of the Utah Jazz,
whose team won a franchise-record-tying 14 games last month, edged
Phoenix's Danny Ainge and Portland's P.J. Carlesimo for Coach of
the Month honors in March.
</P>
<P>
Sloan led Utah to a 14-1 record during the month, tying the
1994-95 Jazz team which posted a 14-1 mark in January of 1995,
despite his team playing only four games at home in the Delta
Center. The Jazz won all four home games and were 10-1 on the
road, including a 6-1 Eastern road trip that lasted 11 days.
</P>
<P>
Utah, which has won nine consecutive games, ended March with a
54-17 record, four-game improvement over the same point last
season.
</P>
<P>
During the month, Sloan moved into 14th place on the all-time
coaching victories list with his 565th win at Denver on March 23.
</P>
<P>
Ainge led Phoenix to a 12-3 record in March and Carlesimo led
Portland to a 13-2 record, including victories in the first 10
games of the month. 
</P>
</TEXT>
