<HEADLINE> Township Enterprises in South China Province Doing Well </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Township-run enterprises in
south China's Guangdong province has scored speedy and sound
development in recent years, according to the provincial
government.
</P>
<P>
These enterprises generated more than 548 billion yuan in
output value in 1996, up nearly 24 percent from the previous year,
and 28 billion yuan in profits, up 13 percent.
</P>
<P>
This growth is a result of enterprises' efforts to apply
technological findings, provide greater publicity for local
name-brand products, and to develop local high-tech industries.
</P>
<P>
The province now has 80 counties, each of which has more than a
billion yuan in sales from township enterprises, and 271 townships
each with over 500 million yuan in sales from such enterprises.
</P>
<P>
It also has more than 27,000 export-oriented township
enterprises that contribute nearly 20 percent to the province's
exports.
</P>
<P>
Exports from Local township enterprises topped 128 billion yuan
last year, a more than 24 percent increase from the previous
year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
