<HEADLINE> Regulations Protect Taiwan Investment in Henan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, April 2 (Xinhua) -- The Henan Provincial People's
Congress has promulgated new regulations to protect Taiwan
investors, starting April 1.
</P>
<P>
Henan Province in central China had approved 832
Taiwan-backed enterprises by the end of 1996, with a total
investment of 910 million US dollars, and over 500 million US
dollars from Taiwan investors.
</P>
<P>
The number of Taiwan-backed enterprises is second only to Hong
Kong.
</P>
<P>
The regulations have ten parts with 25 articles clarifying the
rights of Taiwan investors, the responsibilities of institutions
concerned, and specifying ways to resolve disputes.
</P>
<P>
Zheng Shuzhen, director of the Henan Provincial Office of
Taiwan Affairs, says that the regulations protect the rights and
interests of Taiwan investors and provide for preferential
policies to the investors and enterprises, and in doing so will
encourage more Taiwan business people to invest in Henan. 
</P>
