<HEADLINE> One Killed in Romanian Snowstorm </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, April 1 (Xinhua) -- One passenger was killed and many
have been stranded in a snowstorm in the mountainous area of
central Romania.
</P>
<P>
The blizzard began on Sunday and has paralyzed one of the
country's most important highways. Many cars and buses were
trapped in one-meter-thick snow.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, a rainstorm struck northern Romania, damaging
electrical equipment and cutting electricity to 130 villages and
towns.
</P>
<P>
On Sunday night, part of a cargo ship, the Tismana, sank into
the Danube when the storm turned it upside down.
</P>
<P>
Phone lines in the capital city could not work because
underground cables were affected by accumulated water, and a lot
of big trees were pushed over by strong winds.
</P>
<P>
Meteorologists attributed the storm to an invasion of cold
currents from Northern Europe.
</P>
<P>
Weather forecasts said the climate in Romania would not warm up
for two or three days. 
</P>
</TEXT>
