<HEADLINE> US Provides Loan to Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, April 2 (Xinhua) -- The United States of America will
provide Sri Lanka with a low-interest loan of 10 million US
dollars to buy US wheat, according to government sources today.
</P>
<P>
The sources said that 55,000 metric tons of wheat, representing
about 6 percent of Sri Lanka's annual wheat imports, will be
imported from the United States this year.
</P>
<P>
An agreement on the loan allows Sri Lanka 30 years to repay the
loan with a five-year grace period before the first payment is
due.
</P>
<P>
The interest is 3 percent during the first five years and 4
percent thereafter, the sources added.
</P>
<P>
Sri Lanka has so far received a total of 880 million US dollars
worth of food since 1956.  
</P>
