<HEADLINE> Thai Cabinet Inks Trade Cooperation Memo with China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, April 2 (Xinhua) -- The Thai cabinet has approved in
principle a memorandum of understanding on trade, economic and
technological cooperation between Thailand and China, said a
report from the Thai government house available today.
</P>
<P>
According to the document which passed the cabinet's weekly
meeting on Tuesday, Thailand will promote and facilitate the
purchase of products like chemical fertilizer, pesticide, iron and
steel, machinery and complete plants from China.
</P>
<P>
While, China will promote and facilitate the purchase of Thai
agricultural products as tapioca, rice (including medium-grade
rice), natural rubber and frozen or chilled shrimp in 1997.
</P>
<P>
The two sides also agree to back joint-venture investment in
Thailand in paper manufacturing, commercial maritime fleet,
production of biodegradable packaging made from tapioca and other
crops, fertilizer and rubber tyres, the government house said.
</P>
<P>
In addition, other transport cooperation and technical
assistance will be in the field of construction of dual-track
railway system and the linen fiber technology.
</P>
<P>
The memo will be among the documents to be signed during Thai
prime minister's official visit to China which starts today.
</P>
</TEXT>
