<HEADLINE> Portugal's Population Grows Faster </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LISBON, April 1 (Xinhua) -- Portugal's population last year
grew at nearly three times the average annual rate for the past
decade, the 1996 census shows.
</P>
<P>
The net gain of the population was 4282 persons last year with
the growth rate reaching 1.1 percent, compared with the 0.3
percent annual growth rate in the 10 years from 1984 to 1994.
</P>
<P>
The birth rates in the northern and central areas were higher
than the average rate of the whole country. The country's birth
rate in 1996 increased by 2.5 percent over the previous year.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, the mortality dropped by 10 percent compared
with that of the previous year.
</P>
<P>
Among the 105,772 people who died last year, 52.5 percent of
them were men and 47.5 percent of them were women. One third of
them died of circulatory system diseases and about one fifth died
of malignant tumors. 
</P>
</TEXT>
