<HEADLINE> Thai PM Departs for China on Official Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Thai Prime Minister Chavalit
Yongchaiyudh left here for China this morning on an official visit
at the invitation of his Chinese counterpart Li Peng.
</P>
<P>
The four-day China trip, up till Saturday, is the Thai prime
minister's first overseas visit after his traditional tours of the
six other ASEAN nations.
</P>
<P>
