interim of the Chinese embassy Guan Mu and other Chinese diplomats
were at the airport to see the Thai prime minister off.
</P>
<P>
In Beijing, Chavalit is expected to hold talks with his Chinese
counterpart on enhancement of bilateral economic and trade
relations.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, trade between the two countries has been on
the increase. For several years before 1993, the bilateral two-way
trade was tuned at around 1 billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
In 1994, trade between the two sides for the first time
exceeded the 2 billion dollar mark. And in 1995, it further grew
to top 3.36 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
Last year, even though trade between the two countries faced a
slight slowdown, it still stood at a fairly high level of 3.2
billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
After becoming prime minister on December 1 last year, Chavalit
made traditional familiarization trips to Indonesia, the
Philippines, Brunei, Malaysia, Singapore and Vietnam.  
</P>
