<HEADLINE> Thailand Donates 4 Million U.S. Dollars to ADB </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, April 2 (Xinhua) -- The Thai cabinet Tuesday agreed in
principle to donate 4 million U.S. dollars to the Asia Development
Fund for the 1997-1998 period, a lending arm of the Asia
Development Bank (ADB).
</P>
<P>
According to a press release from the Thai government house
available today, the new donation will strengthen Thailand's role
in the ADB and increase its investment opportunities in other
countries.
</P>
<P>
The Asia Development Fund is a lending facility of the ADB
which offers preferential loans to its members in the Asia-pacific
region.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
