<DOCNO> XIE19970402.0180 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thailand's Price Index Rises in First Quarter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Thailand's consumer price index
(CPI) for the first quarter of this year was 4.4 percent higher
than a year before.
</P>
<P>
However, the latest figures released today by the Business
Economic Department showed a sharp downward trend in inflation on
a year-on-year basis. During the same quarter of last year,
inflation was between 7.3 percent to 7.4 percent.
</P>
<P>
Contributing to the quarterly rise this year were the
increasing prices of the food and beverage, and non-food sectors,
by 5.6 per cent and 3.4 percent respectively, according to the
department's statistics.
</P>
<P>
Prices of rice, pork, chicken, seafood, milk, books, oil,
rents, electricity and water all rose, while vegetable and
detergent markets pulled down product prices because of fierce
competition.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
