<HEADLINE> Chinese Naval Fleet Ends Visit to Mexico </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ACAPULCO, April 1 (Xinhua) -- A Chinese naval fleet headed by
Wang Yongguo, commander of the Chinese navy's South Sea fleet,
left today for Callao, Peru, after concluding its two-day visit to
Mexico's southern port Acapulco.
</P>
<P>
This is the first visit ever to Mexico by a Chinese naval
fleet.
</P>
<P>
During the visit Wang held talks on bilateral relations with
Eugenio Fernandez Strawell, commander of the Mexican Navy's 6th
Region.
</P>
<P>
Before departing for Callao, Wang said that the visit was a
great success, and it strengthened the mutual understanding
between the navies of the two countries. He expressed his wish
that the Mexican navy could visit China in the near future.
</P>
<P>
"We come to Mexico with the amity of the Chinese navy and
people and we leave with the friendship of the Mexican navy and
people," he said.
</P>
<P>
Heriberto Cano Hernandez, inspector general of the Mexican
navy's 6th region, said that the visit by the Chinese navy
strengthened the friendly relations between the Mexican and
Chinese navies.
</P>
<P>
After Peru, the Chinese naval fleet will proceed to Chile.
</P>
</TEXT>
