<DOCNO> XIE19970402.0187 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Woolly Best to Get Quality Mark </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 2 (Xinhua)-- China has launched a nation-wide
quality competition for woolen sweater products to promote the
country's wool industry, today's "China Daily" reported.
</P>
<P>
All woollen sweaters with pure new wool marks are eligible for
the competition, and by October experts will choose 10 to 15
enterprises whose products meet international standards in raw
materials, processing technology and final product quality.
</P>
<P>
The move aims to cultivate China's famous brands in wollen
sweaters and enhance China's market share in the world market,
said John K.H. Sheung, operations manager of International Wool
Secretariat (IWS) China Branch.
</P>
<P>
The wool mark, one of the world's most recognized apparel
marks, is owned by IWS and applied to those products reaching IWS
standards.
</P>
<P>
So far, China has had more than 400 enterprises licenced to use
the pure new wool mark, 200 of which are woolen sweater
enterprises, the paper said.
</P>
<P>
It is reported that China has more than 3,500 wool knitting
enterprises each with annual sales exceeding one million yuan
(120,480 US dollars). However most of the enterprises are small,
and as a result, there is no wollen sweater brand which covers a
considerable domestic market share.
</P>
<P>
The competition, co-organized by IWS and the China Wool Textile
Association, is expected to established industrial leaders for the
woolen sweater industry, said Zhang Bingcheng, head of the
association. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
