<HEADLINE> Hongkong Companies Encouraged to Invest in Guangdong's Retail Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Hongkong investors are being
encouraged to put more funds into the burgeoning consumer market
of Guangdong Province, according to a senior provincial trade
official says.
</P>
<P>
"We believe that cooperation between Guangdong and Hongkong
will be further strengthened after the return of Hongkong to the
embrace of the motherland on July 1," said Ji Liqing, director of
the Guangdong Provincial Trade Commission.
</P>
<P>
"We especially encourage Hongkong investors to finance more
retail, wholesale, distribution and warehouse projects," Ji noted.
</P>
<P>
Investors, many from Hongkong, have built over 300
supermarkets, department stores, convenience shops, and warehouses
in Guangdong. Hongkong has set up numerous joint ventures and
solely-owned enterprises in Guangdong which sell about 30 percent
of their products locally.
</P>
<P>
"The funds, technology and advanced management brought in by
overseas investors are badly needed by Guangdong," the director
explains.
</P>
<P>
"Guangdong is one of the most attractive markets in China. Last
year, retail sales of consumer goods totalled 270 billion yuan,
accounting for over one tenth of the country's total," he
noted. 
</P>
</TEXT>
