<HEADLINE> Chinese Combine Manufacturers Guarantee Quality Before Harvest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 1 (Xinhua) -- Chinese authorities are keeping a
sharper eye on the production and sale of agricultural machinery
as the summer harvest approaches and agricultural equipment
suppliers say they will provide better service for farmers.
</P>
<P>
China's 15 largest harvester makers on Monday jointly issued a
warranty of quality, saying they guarantee quality products and
after-sale service.
</P>
<P>
Gao Yuan'en, director of the Ministry of Machine-Building
Industry's (MMI) Agricultural Equipment Department, noted that
total output of the 15 manufacturers accounts for 95 percent of
the country's harvester output. "Their actions will have a
profound impact on the combine market, markedly improving the
reliability of the products in the marketplace," he said.
</P>
<P>
The combine market has seen a sharp increase since
1994. Statistics from MMI indicate that last year 24,000
harvesters of different sizes were produced, an increase of 150
percent over 1995.
</P>
<P>
China's farm machinery industry last year had an industrial
output value of 85 billion yuan and sales of 81.2 billion yuan,
ranked just behind automobile and electric machines in China's
machine-building industry. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
