<BODY>
<HEADLINE> East China Increasing Efforts at Fighting Pollution </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 2 (Xinhua) -- East China's Jiangsu Province has
announced that 388 major polluters in the area must meet
government pollution standard before the end of the year, or they
will be closed.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government regards pollution control as a
priority in 1997. It listed 388 factories that need major
improvements this year after doing a thorough study, according to
"China Environmental News". Each company puts out 100 tons of
waste water a day.
</P>
<P>
The province has set up four study groups to supervise the
plants' efforts at combating pollution, and has asked the
factories to report their achievements to the local environmental
protection departments every month.
</P>
<P>
It has also encouraged the enterprises that lack financial
support or are unable to make improvements to change their
production.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
