<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Privatized State Enterprises to Be Effective </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar has called for the
transformation of privatized state-owned economic enterprises
(SEE) into effective business organizations in realization of the
state's economic objectives.
</P>
<P>
Quoting Minister for Forestry Chit Swe, today's official paper
The New Light of Myanmar said priority is to be given to
participation of local investors.
</P>
<P>
Chit Swe, in a meeting with personnel of the Ministry's Timber
Enterprise here on Tuesday, stressed the importance of rendering
assistance to attract advanced investments at saw mills in Yangon,
the country's capital.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar announced in January 1995 that it would privatize 51
SEE including saw mills in the first phase and the process of
privatization has been underway in the form of auctioning or
leasing out the SEE or establishing joint ventures with local or
foreign entrepreneurs.
</P>
<P>
Privatization of more than 10 saw mills in Myanmar's Sagaing
division has been underway since the announcement of the SEE
privatization.  
</P>
</TEXT>
