<HEADLINE> Southwest China To Start New Marine Tourism Services </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIHAI, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Beihai, a port city in southwest
China's Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region, will provide marine
tourism services for the Vietnamese cities of Haiphong, Mong Cai
and Ha Long this May.
</P>
<P>
The ship services will be available every Tuesday and Friday,
local sources say. Beihai is now authorized to issue exit and
entry permits for tourism at the Sino-Vietnamese border.
</P>
<P>
As a leading tourist city on the Beibu Gulf, Beihai receives
1.5 million tourists a year. Tourism development was hindered
somewhat in the past because the city was not authorized to issue
the permits for tourists who wanted to visit Vietnam directly and
had to go via Dongxing City.  
</P>
