<DOCNO> XIE19970402.0198 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Asia's Largest Metal Show Set in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 2 ( Xinhua) -- China is to host Asia's largest
metal show, Metal and Metallurgy China'97, featuring the latest
advances in the metals industry, today's "China Daily" reported.
</P>
<P>
On display at the show to be held in the China International
Trade Center in Beijing will be up-to-the-minute products in the
world of metallurgical, casting and forging technologies.
</P>
<P>
The sub-council of metallurgical industry under the China
Council for the Promotion of International Trade announced in
Beijing that the event will start on May 8 and continue until May
12.
</P>
<P>
Over 700 enterprises from 26 countries and regions are already
lined up to take part in the event, the sixth of its kind, the
paper said.
</P>
<P>
Big-name companies such as SMS Schloemann-Siemag AG and Siemens
of Germany, Asea Brown Boveri LTD. of Switzerland, Mitsubishi
Heavy Industries LTD. of Japan and Pohang Iron and Steel Co
LTD. of the Republic of Korea are among those participating.
</P>
<P>
Around 350 Chinese enterprises will also be present, including
representatives from China's top ten steel giants and other
machine-building enterprises.
</P>
<P>
"The event provides a rare chance for the Chinese
metallurgical industries to exchange updated information with
their international partners," said Wang Baojing, vice
secretary-general of the sub-council.
</P>
<P>
The show, the sixth of its kind, will be held as metallurgical
enterprises in China are striving to upgrade their product
quality, creat production varieties and increase their product
values, Wang said.
</P>
<P>
Leading metallurgical enterprises in the world will bring
advanced equipment and models for display.
</P>
<P>
During the show, about 100 lectures focusing on high technology
exchanges and in-depth processing will be presented by foreign
participants. 
</P>
</TEXT>
