<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Miracle Does Take Place </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, April 2 (Xinhua) -- A farmer who was listed as
medically "dead" with extensive damage to six internal organs has
been brought back to life by doctors in a Chinese army hospital.
</P>
<P>
Experts at the General Hospital of Ji'nan Command of the
People's Liberation Army (PLA) in east China's Shandong Province
said it was a miracle that Sun Gaofeng, who was in critical
condition as the result of a gas leak in his home, survived.
</P>
<P>
When Sun entered the hospital for emergency treatment, his
blood pressure was dangerously low, and he suffered from serious
internal bleeding. His liver, kidney and stomach were damaged, and
his heart, lungs and brain were affected.
</P>
<P>
Physicians mapped out a comprehensive treatment plan to keep
Sun alive. After seven days' effort, the farmer was revived. He
remained in the hospital for two months before leaving the
hospital recently. 
</P>
</TEXT>
