<HEADLINE> Russia-Belarus Union Treaty Approved </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 1 (Xinhua) -- The Interparliamentary Conference
of Russia and Belarus today approved the Union Treaty which would
forge closer ties between the two neighboring countries.
</P>
<P>
Russian State Duma Chairman Gennady Seleznev told a press
conference that the majority of the parliamentarians favored the
treaty aiming to promote the integration of Russia and Belarus.
</P>
<P>
The conference called on the presidents of the two countries to
sign the treaty, he said.
</P>
<P>
Seleznev said Russia and Belarus would probably form a
federation state in the future based on the union.
</P>
<P>
The union will be open to other countries, he added.
</P>
<P>
Under the Russia-Belarus Union Treaty, the two countries will
remain independent but keep close coordination on their foreign,
economic and military policies.
</P>
<P>
The presidents of the two countries are scheduled to sign the
treaty Wednesday in Moscow. 
</P>
