<HEADLINE> All Set for Tobacco Auctions in Harare </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, April 1 (Xinhua) -- All is set for the opening of the
tobacco sales floors in Harare on April 22 where farmers are
expected to earn more than 545 million U.S. Dollars over a
six-month selling period.
</P>
<P>
Zimbabwe Tobacco Association Public Relations Director Lal
Taylor said here today a crop of between 205 and 208 million
kilograms is now expected, down from the original forecast of
about 220 million kg.
</P>
<P>
She said it was still early to say what effect the reduced
crop would have on prices, although industry experts were
expecting them to firm around 2.55 to 2.73 U.S. Dollars/kg, the
same obtained at last year's auctions.
</P>
<P>
Tobacco remains one of Zimbabwe's key foreign currency
earners, and last year it was estimated to have brought in nearly
636 million U.S. Dollars. 
