<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 1 (Xinhua) -- France today urged Cambodia to "get
to the bottom of" the grenade attack upon anti-government
demonstrators in Phnom Penh on Sunday, in which 17 people were
killed and more than 100 wounded.
</P>
<P>
While condemning the attack, French foreign ministry spokesman
Yves Doutriaux said that France hopes that the Cambodian
authorities will publish the full truth about the attack and that
"justice be fully exercised."
</P>
<P>
Unidentified attackers riding on driving-by vehicles threw four
grenades at 200 demonstrators protesting what they called
corruption of the country's justice system before the National
Assembly building in Phnom Penh on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The French State Secretary of Francophonie, Margie Sudre, will
begin a visit in Cambodia from Thursday.
</P>
<P>
"This visit will be the occasion to reaffirm the support by
French authorities to the reconstruction of Cambodia as well as
their attachment to the stability and the (building of) state of
law in this country," said the spokesman. 
