<HEADLINE> Ugandan Premier Meets DPRK Vice Premier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, April 1 (Xinhua) -- Ugandan Prime Minister Kintu
Musoke met visiting Deputy Prime Minister and Foreign Affairs
Minister of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK) Kim
Yong Nam here today.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Kintu Musoke assured his guest of his
government's support to the DPRK.
</P>
<P>
Musoke said that Uganda will do everything to keep warm
relationship with the DPRK.
</P>
<P>
Kim Yong Nam said that during his stay in Uganda, he has
witnessed that Uganda has achieved great success under the wise
leadership of President Y. Museveni.
</P>
<P>
He said these achievements include internal security and unity of
Ugandans.
</P>
<P>
He said that he has learned Uganda is strengthening its
defence because this is the only way that a country can achieve
sovereignty and independence.
</P>
<P>
He pledged close cooperation between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Uganda and the DPRK have set bilateral relations since
Uganda's independence in 1962, and the two countries have had
technical cooperation in various fields such as mining,
construction of hydraulic power projects, irrigation,
and agricultural research, among others.
</P>
<P>
The meeting was attended by State Minister for Foreign Affairs in
Charge of Regional Cooperation Rebecca Kadaga.
</P>
<P>
Kim Yong Nam and his delegation arrived in Uganda yesterday
morning for a five-day state visit. enditem

