<HEADLINE> 8 Killed in Car Accident in Upper Egypt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, April 1 (Xinhua) -- Eight persons were killed and nine
others injured when a truck rammed into the rear of the minibus
they were travelling in southern Egypt, the Egyptian MENA news
agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
Officials were quoted as saying the accident happened Monday
night when a truck hit the taxi cab which was heading for Cairo,
the capital of Egypt.
</P>
<P>
The victims were reportedly supporters of the ruling National
Democratic Party returning from a pro-government gathering in
Aswan province, about 800 kilometers south of Cairo.
</P>
<P>
It is the latest in a string of serious traffic accidents in
recent years. In January, an ill-fated bus fell from a bridge in
northern Cairo into the muddy shore of the Nile, killing 39
passengers and injuring at least 29. 
</P>
</TEXT>
