<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-01 18:28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 1 Killed, 5 Wounded in Hezbollah Guerrillas' Attack </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, April 1 (Xinhua) -- One South Lebanon Army (SLA)
militiaman was killed and five others wounded today in an attack
by guerrillas of the Lebanese Shiite Hezbollah, or Party of God,
in south Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
In a statement issued here, the pro-Iranian Hezbollah
announced that its fighters launched attack on an SLA patrol at
10:45 a.m. (0845 GMT) in the western sector of the Israeli
self-proclaimed "security zone" in south Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
The guerrillas used machineguns and rockets in the attack on
a road between the towns of Harfa and Al-Joubbein, destroying a
vehicle, killing and wounding all the SLA militiamen inside, the
statement said.
</P>
<P>
Radio of the Israeli-backed militia confirmed the clash between
guerrillas and the Israeli troops and the SLA militia in the
western part of the border strip at noon, in which one SLA
militiaman was killed and five others wounded.
</P>
<P>
Israel established the 1,100-square-kilometer buffer zone in
1985 in a bid to protect northern Israel from cross-border
guerrilla attacks. Israeli also trained and armed the SLA militia
to patrol the border strip.
</P>
<P>
Israeli troops in the positions of Ali Taher and Babsheh fired
artilleries at vicinities of Nabatieyh Fauqa and Kfar Tibnit at
3:00 p.m. (12:00 GMT), damaging four civilian houses in the
village of Kfar Tibnit and causing no casualties.
</P>
<P>
Security sources in south Lebanon reported that the Israeli
position of Ali Taher was attacked this afternoon by guerrillas,
and no faction has claimed responsibility for the operation.
</P>
<P>
Hit-and-run attacks by Muslim guerrillas and bombardments by
Israeli forces constitute a daily scene in south Lebanon, and
make the area the last active battlefront of the Arab-Israeli
conflict, which has killed six Israeli soldiers and wounded 30 others
since this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
