<DOCNO> XIE19970402.0219 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russia Raises Civil Electricity Tariff </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 1 (Xinhua) --In accordance with a government
resolution Russian regional energy commissions today started to
raise electricity tariffs for residents and reduce it for
industrial consumers, according to the Itar-Tass news agency.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted first deputy head of the federal energy
commission Nikolai Boiko as saying that the electricity tariffs for
Russian residents will be no less than the average cost of
production, transmission and distribution of electricity in a
region.
</P>
<P>
The regional commissions are instructed to gradually reduce and
then eliminate cross-subsidies, Boiko said.
</P>
<P>
This step will cut the tariffs for electric locomotives and
industry by 30 percent, while the industry will save about five
trillion roubles a year.
</P>
<P>
According to Boiko, the current cost price of electricity is
200 roubles per kilowatt/hour in Russia, while the tariff is
205.8 roubles.
</P>
<P>
The tariff for residents is 63 roubles per kilowatt/hour of
electricity. It is planed to raise the tariff for residents to 225
roubles and, in some areas, to 250-270 roubles.
</P>
<P>
It is said that the amount of the tariff in regions depends on
electricity source, communications and other factors.
</P>
<P>
The Russian federal energy commission said that the increase of
the electricity tariffs for residents will be taken into account
of people who receive low incomes and will reach their maximum
only after the reform of housing and communal services. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
