<HEADLINE> Palestinian Official Condemns Israeli Closure </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, April 1 (Xinhua) -- The legislative Palestinian
Council (PC) President, Ahmad Queria (Abu Ala), today condemned
the Israeli government for its closure policy that impeded the
normal work of the Palestinian legislature.
</P>
<P>
Queria has failed to convene a session of the 88-member
council in the West Bank city of Ramallah because there was no
quorum since those Gaza council members were barred from
traveling to Ramallah due to the border closure, according to a
report of JMCC, a Palestinian press service based in East
Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
Queria said that the Israeli measures are aimed at blowing up
the peace process. He vowed to make every effort to revive the
PC work so as to foil the plans of the Israeli government to
obstruct the process of establishing an independent Palestinian
state.
</P>
<P>
Some PC members from the West Bank held informal discussions
on the current political situation. Haidar Abdul Shafi called
for suspending the work of the council until all members show up
in Ramallah. Most other members expressed their opposition to
his idea, stressing that the council should continue its normal
functions and deal with ongoing events as they happen.
</P>
<P>
Hassan Asfour, PC member and member of Palestinian negotiating
team, sternly criticized Palestinian National Authority
Information Minister Yasser Abed Rabbo for his meeting with a
senior Israeli official in Jerusalem Monday night.
</P>
<P>
Asfour described the meeting as irresponsible, adding that it
breached the Palestinian decision not to hold any meetings or
contacts with Israeli officials.
</P>
<P>
"It is time for everyone to abide by the Palestinian and Arab
decisions regarding freezing normalization," he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
