<HEADLINE> Turkish President: Peace in Bosnia Must Be Ensured </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, April 1 (Xinhua) -- Turkish President Suleyman Demirel
said here today that there was no more bloodshed in Bosnia after
Dayton Agreement, but this is not enough.
</P>
<P>
Demirel made the remarks at his meeting with visiting High
Representative Carl Bildt responsible for the implementation of
Dayton Agreement's civilian issues.
</P>
<P>
Demirel pointed out that a failure to implement Dayton
Agreement would fully lead to spoiling of existing stability in
the region, adding "under all conditions, independence,
sovereignty and territorial integrity of Bosnia should be
preserved."
</P>
<P>
Judgement of war criminals and return of civilians should be
realized as soon as possible, said the Turkish president.
</P>
<P>
Before the meeting, Bildt said that the situation in Bosnia
was in disorder and expressed his satisfaction over Turkey's
positive role on the issue of Bosnia-Herzegovina.
</P>
<P>
Bildt is currently in Turkey to attend a meeting of Bosnia
Peace Monitoring Committee Steering Group, scheduled to be held
in Istanbul Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Before his meeting with Bildt, Turkish Prime Minister
Necmettin Erbakan said that Turkey "has attributed a great
importance to the protection of borders and preserving of the
integrity to provide the establishment of peace in Bosnia."
</P>
</TEXT>
