<HEADLINE> 56 PKK Rebels Killed in Southeastern Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, April 1 (Xinhua) -- Turkish security forces killed 56
rebels of the outlawed Kurdish Worker's Party (PKK) in the past
three days during their military operations against the
anti-government organization, a military statement said today.
</P>
<P>
The statement issued by the General Secretariate of Turkey's
General Staff said that Turkey's 3rd Army Commandership launched
air and ground attacks on PKK guerrillas in Aliboazi region of
Tunceli province, killing 43 PKK rebels in the clashes over the
past three days.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, 23rd Gendarme Border Division Commandership clashed
with the PKK rebels in Kupelidagi region of Sirnak province
bordering Iraq and 13 PKK militants were killed in the conflict,
said the statement.
</P>
<P>
More than 21,000 people, including PKK rebels, government
troops and civilians, have been killed in armed clashes since
August 1984 when the PKK started fighting for autonomy in the
southeast of Turkey. 
</P>
</TEXT>
