<HEADLINE> Angolan Ruling Party Urges for Solutions to </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, April 1 (Xinhua) -- The Popular Movement for the
Liberation of Angola (MPLA), the country's ruling party, urged
here today for earliest solutions to military problems in the
peace process.
</P>
<P>
Issues such as enroling fighters of the former rebel National
Union for the Total Independence of Angola (UNITA) into a
unified army and a national police force should be solved as
soon as possible, MPLA said in a communique.
