<HEADLINE> EU Delegation Visits Algeria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALGIERS, April 1 (Xinhua) -- An EU delegation led by Dutch
Foreign Minister Hans Van Mierlo whose country holds the EU'
rotating presidency, arrived here today.
</P>
<P>
The delegation was greeted upon arrival by Algerian Foreign
Minister Ahmed Attaf.
</P>
<P>
In his arrival statement, Mierlo said the aim of his visit to
Algeria was to discuss with Algerian government officials the
progress achieved by the Euro-Mediterranean partnership as well
as the relations between the EU and Algeria.
</P>
<P>
The visit was also aimed at preparing for a conference between
the 15-nation EU and 12 Mediterranean countries to take place on
April 15-16 in Malta.
</P>
<P>
Algerian President Liamine Zeroual will meet with Mierlo
during his stay here. The EU delegation will be holding talks
with Algerian officials on the issue of partnership and the
Euro-Algerian negotiations on a partnership agreement. 
</P>
