<HEADLINE> GCC Chief Concludes Visit to UAE </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABIE, April 1 (Xinhua) -- The Secretary General of the
Gulf Cooperation Council (GCC) Jamil Al Hojeilan said today that
Jerusalem is the principal cause of the Arab nation.
</P>
<P>
Hojeilan, at the end of his two-day visit here, urged the Arab
states to unify their efforts to confront the present challenge,
referring to the stalled Middle East peace process.
</P>
<P>
The peace process has come across great difficulties since two
weeks ago when Israel carried out its Jewish settlement plan in
East Jerusalem, a place the Palestinians see as the capital of
their future state, despite fierce opposition and criticism from
the world, particularly the Arab nations.
</P>
<P>
Hojeilan was received here this afternoon by UAE President Sheikh
Zayid Bin Sultan Al Nahyan.
</P>
<P>
He praised the UAE attitude in support of Arab causes including
that of Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
Hojeilan is visiting the UAE within the framework of a GCC tour
to follow up the implementation of the resolutions adopted by the
GCC summit in Doha last December. He had earlier visited Qatar
where he had a meeting with the Emir of Qatar Sheikh Hamad Bin
Khalifa Al Thani.
</P>
<P>
The GCC groups Bahrain, Kuwait, Oman, Qatar, Saudi Arabia, and
the UAE. 
</P>
</TEXT>
