<HEADLINE> UN Appeals for 68.2 Mln Dlrs to Aid Sierra Leone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, April 1 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations today
appealed for 68.2 million dollars to address the humanitarian
needs in Sierra Leone following five years of civil conflict.
</P>
<P>
After the civil conflict formally ended with the signing of the
Abidjan peace accord on November 30, 1996, over a half million of
the estimated 1.6 million displaced people have returned to their
areas of origin, according to the UN Department of Humanitarian
Affairs.
</P>
<P>
The humanitarian program in the appeal for the period from
March 1997 to February 1998 was designed to promote the
consolidation of peace and assist the affected population in
attaining higher level of self-sufficiency.
</P>
<P>
The program included food aid to sustain people displaced or
impoverished by the war, to facilitate their return to their
communities and to support them when they strive to produce their
own sustenance. 
</P>
</TEXT>
