<HEADLINE> French Foreign Minister to Visit Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, April 1 (Xinhua) -- French Foreign Minister Herve De
Charette will start a two-day official visit to Turkey Wednesday
to exchange views with Turkish officials on Turkey's bid for its
full membership of the European Union (EU).
</P>
<P>
De Charette is on visits to Azerbaijan and Armenia, which are
troubled by the Nagorno-Karabakh issue. He will inform Turkish
officials of the results of his visits to the above two countries.
</P>
<P>
The Anatolia News Agency today quoted diplomatic sources here
as saying that De Charette's visit to Turkey means that "Turkey is
perceived as the most important country, which can make
contributions to the solution of the Nagorno-Karabakh question
together with co-chairmen of Minsk Group in OSCE."
</P>
<P>
Azerbaijan and Armenia stopped their long conflicts in 1995
over the possession of the region of Nagorno-Karabakh, which seeks
sought independence from Azerbaijan. But the two sides'
negotiation efforts failed to make progress last year on the
status of the region in the future and the conditions for the stay
of the peacekeeping troops of the Organization for Security and
Cooperation in Europe (OSCE).
</P>
<P>
OSCE Minsk Group started a three-day meeting today on the
Nagorno-Karabakh question in Moscow with the participation of the
parties concerned.
</P>
<P>
De Charette is expected to reiterate French support for
Turkey's bid for full EU membership during his stay here. 
</P>
</TEXT>
