<HEADLINE> UNFPA Launches New Campaign for Gender Equality </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, April 1 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations Persons
Fund (UNFPA) announced today a new initiative under the banner
theme of "Men are Women Too" for gender equality.
</P>
<P>
As a first step, the UNFPA is proposing a world conference on
the subject. To be called "Women 2" in reference to the Fourth
World Conference on Women in 1995, it will have a parallel
process.
</P>
<P>
Men will form the majority of the delegations, though they will
usually be led by a woman to ensure consistency. They will have
equal access to a 12-chapter platform for action covering topics
heretofore closed to men such as child care, family health,
education, responsibility for food, fuel and water and making sure
they arrive home before the pubs close, according to the UNFPA.
</P>
<P>
The UNFPA set up a new Division for Engenderment Empowerment
and Development for the initiative. "There is a whole world of men
out there who should also be participating in the development
process, driving us towards food security, protecting the
environment, ending poverty and leading us down the road to a
sustainable future," said A. P. Rillfoal, chief of the new
division. 
</P>
</TEXT>
