<HEADLINE> Mozambique, Swaziland to Reopen Goma Border Post </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Goma thus will become the second border checkpoint between the
two countries, Roque Muquessuane, the Magistrate of Namaacha
County in Maputo Province, said here today.
</P>
<P>
A 10-kilometer road between Goma and Namaacha, where the sole
border station is now located, has been rebuilt, Roque was quoted
by the Mozambican Information Agency as saying.
</P>
<P>
War-damaged power plants, houses for immigrates
and Customs officers and other infrastructure in Goma will be
renovated soon after an Italian firm figures out the sum of
money the renovation needs, he said.
</P>
<P>
There is also a railway station in Goma but it is damaged, he
added.
</P>
<P>
Goma, nearer to some of Swaziland's towns compared with
Namaacha, is of vital importance for Mozambique to boost trade
with Swaziland and fight smuggles of arms and drugs and other
illegal activities, he noted.
</P>
<P>
Swaziland is located between South Africa and Mozambique.
