<HEADLINE> German Submarines Start 1st Post-War Cross-Atlantic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, April 1 (Xinhua) -- For the first time since the end of
World War II, two German submarines started to cross the Atlantic
today for a training journey to the United States, news reports
said.
</P>
<P>
The two submarines, known as U-17 and U-26, started from the
Eckernforde base of the third submarine squadron of the German
navy Bundesmarine today. They are also expected to participate in
joint maneuvers with the U.S. military, the German news agency
DPA reported. 
</P>
