<HEADLINE> China Urges US to Return to Road of Dialogue, </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, April 1 (Xinhua) -- Alternate Representative of the
Chinese delegation Li Baodong today urged the United States to
return to the road of dialogue and cooperation by putting an end
to all actions of confrontation.
</P>
<P>
In exercising the right of reply to a speech made by William
Richardson, US permanent representative to the UN, at the 53rd
session of the Commission on Human Rights, Li said, "The US
representatives have a bad habit. They are fond of pointing their
fingers at other countries' affairs, as if the US is the master of
the world and all countries have to listen to it. This is
anachronism."
</P>
<P>
"The US representative probably forgot that the human rights
situation in the US today is far from brilliant and the scourge of
racism is still running rampant," Li pointed out. "This is a fact
that even the US government itself cannot but admit. Isn't it more
advisable that the US representative takes more care of his own
domestic affairs and puts his own house in order?"
</P>
<P>
Li said, "The US representative remarked in his address that
the US would not seek confrontation with China. We welcome this
desire of non-confrontation. However, it is in the same address
that he flagrantly provoked confrontation. This is most
unfortunate and self-contradictory."
</P>
<P>
"Dialogue and confrontation are incompatible, and you can't
have both," Li stressed. "If the US really has the desire to cease
confrontation, it should manifest it in concrete deeds by putting
an end to all actions of confrontation and returning to the road
of dialogue and cooperation."
</P>
<P>
Richardson was also counterattacked by countries like Cuba,
Iraq and Myanmar, which he named in his speech. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
