<HEADLINE> Dow Climbing Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, April 1 (Xinhua) -- The Dow Jones industrials
finished higher today after a day of shedding on a set of economic
reports that worsened the fear for more interest hikes.
</P>
<P>
The Dow climbed 27.57 points to close at 6611.05, regaining a
bit of the nearly 300-point loss it suffered in the previous two
sessions.
</P>
<P>
Optimistic investors seized on a small part of a report from
the National Association of Purchasing Management released this
morning. But the purchasing managers' index of overall economic
activity rose. In addition, the federal government reported the
highest construction spending increase in 11 months and the
Conference Board's leading economic indicators index posted its
biggest gain in a year.
</P>
<P>
But there is no consensus among investment professionals that a
more protracted decline looms.
</P>
<P>
Yet the market has stood some violent selloffs over the past
year and ordinary investors have barely flinched, keeping stock
and viewing price pullbacks as buying opportunities.
</P>
<P>
The recent selloff began with concerns that the Federal Reserve
would raise interest rates to forestall inflation, which it did
last Tuesday. 
</P>
