<HEADLINE> Hi-tech Innovation Center Set Up in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 2 (Xinhua) -- A 16,000-sq-m innovation center
has been set up in Shanghai's Caohejing Hi-tech Park at a cost of
60 million yuan, to boost its hi-tech industry.
</P>
<P>
The innovation center is intended to promote the park's self
development ability and to apply scientific discoveries and
improve scientific exchanges, according to Wang Zhihong, president
of the Caohejing hi-tech development company.
</P>
<P>
The innovation center will try to attract people with
preferential policies for rents and taxes, he said.
</P>
<P>
It was approved as a hi-tech park by the State Council in March
1993 and has become an industrial base with the highest technology
concentration in Shanghai, and is home to more than 300
technology-intensive enterprises, with several thousand personnel.
</P>
<P>
There are 600 enterprises in the hi-tech park, including 210
foreign-funded ones. Last year, it had a per capita sales output
of 210,000 yuan, several times that of the average for the rest of
the city. 
</P>
