<HEADLINE> U.S. Military Plane Crashes In Honduras </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEGUCIGALPA, April 1 (Xinhua) -- A U.S. Air Force Mercules
C-130 plane crashed in flames this morning after overrunning a
landing strip at Tegucigalpa's Toncotin International Airport,
killing three people on board. air terminal's authorities said.
</P>
<P>
The transport plane skidded up to a highway on which, no vehicle
was circulating at the time when the crash occurred.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. cargo plane took off from Panama on a routine fueling
mission, according to spokespersons from the U.S. embassy
in the country.
</P>
<P>
Airport authorities said the plane made a normal south-north
landing but apparently the runway was not long enough for it to
come to a complete stop so it overran the strip and crashed
against part of the "Camosa" bridge and then dropped onto a two-lane
highway leading to the capital city.
</P>
<P>
Of a total of ten people on board, three were killed instantly
and seven others injured. They were rescued by Metropolitan
firefighters and National Investigation agents.
</P>
<P>
The accident occurred at 09:45 local time and the seven injured
as well as the three completed-burned bodies were flown to the
Southern Command based in Panama three hours later. 
</P>
</TEXT>
