<HEADLINE> Economy in Uruguay Continues to Rise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO, April 1 (Xinhua) -- The economy in Uruguay
maintained its growth in the first two months of this year,
according to the Uruguayan Central Bank.
</P>
<P>
In January and February, meat exports increased by 63.3 percent
and beef by 27.4 percent, compared with the first two months of
1996.
</P>
<P>
During the same period, the sales of cement for public works
grew by 46.3 percent, and for private construction by nine
percent, while the electrical energy was up 17.7 percent and
overall domestic consumption of energy by 7.2 percent.
</P>
<P>
Automobile sales were 26.1 percent higher than those reported
in the first two months of 1996. 
</P>
