<HEADLINE> Three WBA Champions Lined up for Title Defences </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, April 1 (Xinhua) -- The World Boxing Association
(WBA) announced in Caracas on Tuesday that three of their
titleholders would defend their crowns in April.
</P>
<P>
American fighter Virgil Hill, the 1984 Olympic gold medallist
and world light heavyweight champion since 1987, will fight the
German World Boxing Organisation (WBO) holder Darius Michalczewski
in Hamburg on April 19.
</P>
<P>
Ike Quartey of Ghana, who won the title by knocking out
Venezuelan Crisanto Espana in June 1994, will defend his
welterweight title against Tiger Jones in Las Vegas on April 18
and Super middleweight champion Frank Liles of the United States
is slated to fight the Ecuadorian Segundo Mercado in mid-April.
</P>
</TEXT>
