<BODY>
<HEADLINE> OPEC Oil Price Drops to 18.59 Dollars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, April 1 (Xinhua) -- The average price of OPEC's basket
of seven crude oils fell last week to 18.59 U.S. dollars per
barrel, representing a 35-cent decline over the previous week.
</P>
<P>
According to the Vienna-based Secretariat of the Organization
of Petroleum Exporting Countries, the average oil price in March
as a whole stood at 18.69 dollars a barrel, 1.8 dollars lower than
February.
</P>
<P>
The OPEC benchmark price is 21 dollars per barrel. 
</P>
</TEXT>
