<HEADLINE> Seles Advances at Hilton Head Island </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 1 (Xinhua) -- Monica Seles scored a swift
second-round victory over Wang Shi-ting of Chinese Taipei at the
Family Circle Cup in Hilton Head Island, South Carolina, on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The fourth-seeded Seles, who received a first-round bye, posted
a 6-3, 6-3 win in 57 minutes.
</P>
<P>
The former world nubmer one, now ranked fifth, reached the
final on hard court at the Lipton Championships last week in her
first tourament of the year.
</P>
<P>
Fifth-seeded two-time champion Conchita Martinez of Spain had a
much tougher time than Seles before pulling out a 6-7, 6-4, 6-3
second-round victory over qualifier Olga Barabanschikova of
Belarus.
</P>
<P>
In a first-round encounter, Jennifer Capriati upset 11th-seeded
fellow American Mary Joe Fernandez 6-3, 4-6, 7-6 in a match that
featured 18 service breaks.
</P>
<P>
The 21-year-old Capriati, who won the third-set tie-break 7-3,
had reached the final here in 1990 as a 14-year-old.
</P>
<P>
Top seed Martina Hingis, who became the world's top-ranked
player on Monday, was set to play the tournament's first-ever
night match against Germany's Barbara Rittner later Tuesday.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
