<HEADLINE> Officials in Northwest China Held Accountable For Poverty Relief </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Northwest China's Ningxia Hui
Autonomous Region is fighting its last and decisive battle to
eradicate absolute poverty by the turn of this century.
</P>
<P>
More than 3,000 officials are sent to China's poorest Xihaigu
area, responsible for poverty relief of over 500 villages, and
they will not leave the areas before sound alleviation has been
ensured, according to Zhou Shengxian, vice-chairman of the
regional government.
</P>
<P>
The region has reduced the number of its poverty-stricken
population to 760,000 over the past years, and is to help another
200,000 shake off poverty this year. Efforts will be focused on
villages which have less than 500 yuan of income and 150 kilograms
of grain per capita annually.
</P>
<P>
Concern from the society-at-large contributes to the work. More
than 11.3 million yuan were donated to the area last year. And
top priority is given to spreading agro-science, infrastructure
construction, and labour force transfer, to help the poor develop
production.
</P>
<P>
The Ningxia Military Region and the Regional Department of
Geology and Mineral Resources carried out a program of drilling
100 wells to aid the poor and a "special-water-prospecting-plan"
in the area last year, respectively, and drilled 102 wells for 94
villages to provide clean water for 200,000 rural residents and
two million head of livestock.
</P>
<P>
A total of 2,200 wells were drilled, 70 kilometres of high
voltage electricity transmission lines erected, and some 566 ha of
farmland improved in the area last year, the vice-chairman says.
enditem

nnnn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
