<HEADLINE> Qinghai Province Acting Governor And Party Chief Appointed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 2 (Xinhua) -- The governor of northwest China's
Qinghai Province, Tian Chengping, has been appointed provincial
party chief, and the deputy party chief of the Inner Mongolia
Autonomous Region, Bai Enpei, has been made the province's acting
governor.
</P>
<P>
The provincial people's congress of Qinghai Tuesday accepted
Tian's resignation as governor, and elected Bai to the new post.
</P>
<P>
Tian, who is a native of north China's Hebei Province, was born
in 1945, and graduated from Qinghua University in 1968. He worked
in Beijing before moving to Qinghai to work in 1988. His
appointment was made by the Central Committee of the Communist
Party of China.
</P>
<P>
Bai, a native of Shaanxi Province, was born in 1946, and
graduated from Northeast Polytechnic University in 1970.  
</P>
</TEXT>
