<HEADLINE> More Foreign Tourists Visit Venezuela in 1996 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, April 1 (Xinhua) -- The number of foreigners visiting
Venezeuala rose 25 percent last year to 800,000 and is expected
to rise to more than one million by 1998, an official report said
here today.
</P>
<P>
Some 45 percent of the visitors are from Europe, mainly
Germany, Holland, Spain and Denmark, according to the report by
the National Council of Promotion and Investment (CONAPRI).
</P>
<P>
Americans accounted for 29 percent of foreign visitors.
</P>
<P>
The latest survey of visitors during the off-peak season shows
43.5 percent of the foreign visitors are here on vacation, with
41.2 percent on business.
</P>
<P>
Three quarters of the tourists stayed in hotels costing an
average 112 U.S. dollars a day and stayed for an average of 10
days, the survey said. But only 5.6 percent of them were on
package tours. 
</P>
</TEXT>
