<HEADLINE> Booming Export-Oriented Economy in Jiangsu Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, April 2 (Xinhua) -- East China's Jiangsu Province
scored overall development in foreign trade, overseas investment,
and technological cooperation during the first two months of this
year.
</P>
<P>
Jiangsu, one of the most developed areas in China, handled
imports and exports totaling 2.4 billion US dollars during that
period, a 60 percent increase from the same period in 1996, with
exports increasing 32 percent to nearly 1.6 billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
The province now has 64 counties and county-level cities that
can handle foreign trade directly, and the number of provincial
state enterprises which are authorized to directly handle foreign
trade is expected to rise from the present 600 to 1,000 by the end
of the year.
</P>
<P>
It has more than 15,000 operational foreign-funded enterprises,
which contribute a lot to the foreign economic development,
scoring an 80 percent increase in Jiangsu's exports during the
first two months of this year.
</P>
<P>
Actual overseas investment in the province during the two-month
period was 610 million US dollars, an increase of nearly 20
percent over the same period in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the province signed 184 million US dollars
worth of contracts to undertake overseas construction and
providing labor services to foreign clients.
</P>
<P>
The local tourism industry helped the province attract about
110,000 overseas visitors during the two months, a rise of 36
percent over the same period of 1996. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
