<DOCNO> XIE19970402.0294 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> No Political Obstacles Between China, Ukraine </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, April 1 (Xinhua) -- There are no political obstacles
between China and Ukraine, which has enabled bilateral relations
to develop to a high level, Chinese Vice Premier Wu Bangguo said
during his meeting with Ukrainian Foreign Minister Gennady
Udovenko Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Wu, who arrived in Kiev on March 31 for his three-day official
visit, said both countries handle problems between them with a
long-term view. It benefits the two peoples and states, Wu added.
</P>
<P>
It is the wish of not only the Ukrainian government but the
Ukrainian people to maintain friendship with China, Udovenko said.
</P>
<P>
The foreign minister said the Ukrainian government sticks to
the One-China Policy and supports Chinese positions on issues such
as Taiwan and Tibet.
</P>
<P>
Ukraine also backs China's stance on human rights, Udovenko
stressed. No country has the right to impose its own standards on
any other nations.
</P>
<P>
Wu added that China will as usual support the Ukrainian
sovereignty, independence and territorial integrity.
</P>
<P>
Kiev is the first stop of Wu's 15-day visit to Ukraine,
Belarus, the Czech Republic, Finland and Switzerland. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
